               <head>Miscellaneous works on Sufism, 17 works (a-q)</head>
               <msContents class="http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2008112367 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2006003807">
                  <summary>Collection of miscellaneous works on Sufism. Volume not dated, though items b, d, and f are dated by different scribes to Muḥarram 1119/April 1707, with item b written in <placeName>Gavālyār</placeName> (<origPlace>Gwalior</origPlace>). Written in fine naskh and rough to fine nastaʿlīq in parts by multiple hands. Incomplete summary of contents added at beginning (f. 1r and preceding flyleaf). Original text frames cut and remounted with new gutter margins. Folios subsequently rebound in IOL red half leather binding, stamp dated 18 Feb 1936; folios damaged heavily by wormholes; net overlay throughout; ink smudged and bleeding in parts. Beginning flyleaf bears, along with copious selections of verse, an owner’s valuation note on in raqm/siyāq for 2 [rūpyah], and a large circular seal impression: <persName key="person_f7749" role="asn">Kāmyāb Khān</persName> fidavī-yi <persName key="person_f7750" role="asn">Muḥammad Shāh Pādshāh Ghāzī</persName> [RY] sanah 2, 1132/1720. Labels from the earlier loose paper wrapper (text on nineteenth-century legislation) remounted on the flyleaf before the first folio. One of these labels records the name <persName key="person_f7751" role="asn">Sayyid Qudrat Allāh</persName>. Another larger label expands the summary of contents.
                  </summary>
                  <msItem n="1" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_1180-item1">
                     <locus from="1v" to="17v">ff. 1v-17v</locus>
                     <note>
                        <p>Item a. </p>
                        <p>Theosophical treatise on conceptions of tawḥīd or divine unity and its implications for space and time, by an unnamed author. </p>
                        <p>
Not dated at end. 
</p>
                        <p>Neat, miniscule scribal nastaʿlīq, with Arabic quotations in naskh. Blurring of text on subsequent folios. Damage by wormholes. 
</p>
                        <p>Recto of folio 1 states a partially erased note on custody: <persName key="person_f7402" role="fmo">Muḥammad Sharīf</persName>, Ramaz̤ān RY 25 of <persName key="viaf_45680638" role="oth">Emperor Muḥammad Shāh</persName> (1155/November 1742). 
                        </p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="per" otherLangs="ara">Persian and Arabic</textLang>
                     <title xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="work_8521">Ghāyat al-imkān fī dirāyat al-zamān</title>
                     <title xml:lang="per" key="work_8521">غاية الامكان فى دراية الزّمان</title>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem n="2" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_1180-item2">
                     <locus from="18v" to="51v">ff. 18v-51v</locus>
                     <author>
                        <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" type="supplied" key="ark:/81055/vdc_100164658478.0x000001 viaf_485149294387580522619">Aḥrār, ʿUbayd Allāh ibn Maḥmūd, 1403 or 1404-1489 or 1490</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="per" type="supplied" key="ark:/81055/vdc_100164658478.0x000001 viaf_485149294387580522619">خواجه احرار</persName>
                     </author>
                     <note>
                        <p>Item b. </p>
                        <p>Untitled collection of the dicta or fiqarāt ascribed to the Ṣūfī saint, <persName key="ark:/81055/vdc_100166176974.0x000001 viaf_485149294387580522619" role="ant">Khvājah ʿUbayd Allāh Aḥrār</persName> (d. circa 895/1490). 
                        </p>
                        <p>Dated colophon (f. 51v): completed after ẓuhr, 28 Z̲ī Ḥijjah (year left blank, 1118?/2 April 1707), in the city of <placeName>Gavālyār</placeName> (<origPlace>Gwalior</origPlace>). 
                        </p>
                        <p>Miniscule scribal nastaʿlīq, with Arabic quotations in red ink. Blurring of text on subsequent folios. Damage by wormholes. 
</p>
                        <p>Annotations in margins. 
</p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="per" otherLangs="ara">Persian and Arabic</textLang>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem n="3" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_1180-item3">
                     <locus from="52r" to="52v">ff. 52r-52v</locus>
                     <note>
                        <p>Item c. </p>
                        <p>Brief notes translating traditions of the <persName key="viaf_97245226" role="ant">Prophet Muḥammad</persName>. 
                        </p>
                        <p>Not dated at end. 
</p>
                        <p>Scribal nastaʿlīq. 
</p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="per">Persian </textLang>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem n="4" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_1180-item4">
                     <locus from="53r" to="64v">ff. 53r-64v</locus>
                     <textLang mainLang="per">Persian </textLang>
                     <note>
                        <p>Item d. </p>
                        <p>Treatise in defence of the Ṣūfī practice of samāʿ or audition (in z̲ikr) based on several <orgName>Naqshbandī</orgName> authorities in prose and verse, by <persName key="person_f7056" role="aut">Aḥmad ibn Jalāl al-Dīn Kāshānī Khiljī</persName> (d. 949/1542), whose practices had been characterised by the <orgName>ʿulamāʾ</orgName> as contrary to the Sunnah.
                        </p>
                        <p>Dated colophon (f. 64v): completed by <persName key="person_f7637" role="scr">Valī Muḥammad</persName> on Monday, 14 Muḥarram 1119/17 April 1707. 
                        </p>
                        <p>Marginal annotations. 
</p>
                        <p>Miniscule scribal nastaʿlīq. Blurring of text on subsequent folios. </p>
                        <p>Damage by wormholes. 
</p>
                     </note>
                     <title xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="work_21722">Risālah-'i samāʿīyah</title>
                     <title xml:lang="per" key="work_21722">رسالهٴ سماعيّه</title>
                     <author>
                        <persName key="person_f7056" type="supplied" xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc">Aḥmad ibn Jalāl al-Dīn Kāshānī Khiljī</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="per" type="supplied" key="person_f7056">احمد ابن جلال الدّين كاشانى خلجى</persName>
                     </author>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem n="5" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_1180-item5">
                     <locus from="65r" to="65r">f. 65r</locus>
                     <textLang mainLang="per">Persian </textLang>
                     <note>
                        <p>Item e. </p>
                        <p>Untitled note on faqr or poverty by an unnamed author. 
</p>
                        <p>Not dated at end. 
</p>
                        <p>Miniscule scribal nastaʿlīq. Blurring of text. Damage by wormholes. 
</p>
                     </note>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem n="6" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_1180-item6">
                     <locus from="65r" to="75r">ff. 65r-75r</locus>
                     <textLang mainLang="per" otherLangs="ara">Persian and Arabic</textLang>
                     <note>
                        <p>Item f. </p>
                        <p>Commentary on a ḥadīs̲ or tradition regarding two states of reality by an author whose identity remains unclear. 
</p>
                        <p>Dated colophon (f. 75r): completed 22 Muḥarram 1119/25 April 1707. 
</p>
                        <p>Miniscule scribal nastaʿlīq, Arabic quotations overlined in red. Blurring of text on subsequent folios. Damage by wormholes. 
</p>
                     </note>
                     <title xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="work_21715">Risālah-'i vujūdīyah</title>
                     <title xml:lang="per" key="work_21715">رسالهٴ وجوديّه</title>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem n="7" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_1180-item7">
                     <locus from="76r" to="94r">ff. 76r-94r</locus>
                     <textLang mainLang="per" otherLangs="ara">Persian and Arabic</textLang>
                     <note>
                        <p>Item g. </p>
                        <p>Untitled Ṣūfī treatise on man’s relationship with God and creation by an unnamed author. 
</p>
                        <p>Not dated at end. 
</p>
                        <p>Miniscule scribal nastaʿlīq, coarsening after folio 79 probably by a different hand. Blurring of text on subsequent folios. Damage by wormholes. 
</p>
                     </note>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem n="8" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_1180-item8">
                     <locus from="95v" to="103r">ff. 95v-103r</locus>
                     <textLang mainLang="per" otherLangs="ara">Persian and Arabic</textLang>
                     <note>
                        <p>Item h. </p>
                        <p>Untitled Ṣūfī commentary on a formula relating to creation based on early authorities, by an unnamed author. 
</p>
                        <p>Not dated at end. 
</p>
                     </note>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem n="9" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_1180-item9">
                     <locus from="104r" to="114r">ff. 104r-114r</locus>
                     <textLang mainLang="per" otherLangs="ara">Persian and Arabic</textLang>
                     <note>
                        <p>Item i. </p>
                        <p>Ṣūfī commentary on a verse from the <title>Qurʾān</title> (2:33), supplemented with traditions of the <persName key="viaf_97245226" role="ant">Prophet Muḥammad</persName>, by an unnamed author. 
                        </p>
                        <p>The present title appears in an endorsement at the beginning and the concluding subscription. 
</p>
                        <p>Not dated at end. 
</p>
                     </note>
                     <title xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="work_21724">Risālat al-sharīfah al-bukāʾīyah</title>
                     <title xml:lang="per" key="work_21724">رسالة الشّريفة البكائيّه</title>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem n="10" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_1180-item10">
                     <locus from="115v" to="120v">ff. 115v-120v</locus>
                     <note>
                        <p>Item j. </p>
                        <p>Untitled treatise on the conformity of Ṣūfī principles with the Sunnah by an unnamed author. 
</p>
                        <p>Colophon (f. 120v): completed by <persName key="person_f7012" role="scr">ʿAbd al-Ghanī Mawdūdī al-Ḥasanī (?) al-Ḥusaynī (?)</persName>. 
                        </p>
                        <p>Not dated at end. 
</p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="per" otherLangs="ara">Persian and Arabic</textLang>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem class="http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2010108002" n="11" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_1180-item11">
                     <locus from="121v" to="125r">ff. 121v-125r</locus>
                     <textLang mainLang="per" otherLangs="ara">Persian and Arabic</textLang>
                     <note>
                        <p>Item k. </p>
                        <p>Ṣūfī treatise commenting on the Islamic creed as recorded in the prayer <title>Āmantu bi-Allāh</title>, by an unnamed author. 
                        </p>
                        <p>Not dated at end. 
</p>
                     </note>
                     <title xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="work_21742"> Sharḥ-i Āmantu bi-Allāh</title>
                     <title xml:lang="per" key="work_21742">شرح آمنت بالله</title>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem n="12" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_1180-item12">
                     <locus from="126r" to="126v">ff. 126r-126v</locus>
                     <textLang mainLang="per" otherLangs="ara">Persian and Arabic</textLang>
                     <note>
                        <p>Item l. </p>
                        <p>Brief untitled Ṣūfī account of traditions relating to <persName key="person_f7588" role="subject">Shaykh ʿĪsá Sindhī</persName> by an unnamed author. 
                        </p>
                        <p>Not dated at end. 
</p>
                     </note>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem n="13" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_1180-item13">
                     <locus from="127r" to="131r">ff. 127r-131r</locus>
                     <textLang mainLang="per" otherLangs="ara">Persian and Arabic</textLang>
                     <note>
                        <p>Item m. </p>
                        <p>Untitled speculative disquisition positing an alternative account on the origins of the universe, the prophets, first four caliphs, and saints, ending with a supplementary notice on <persName key="ark:/81055/vdc_100164658827.0x000001 viaf_88126052" role="subject">Abū Ḥanīfah</persName>, by an unnamed author. 
                        </p>
                        <p>Not dated at end. 
</p>
                     </note>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem n="14" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_1180-item14">
                     <locus from="131v" to="131v">f. 131v</locus>
                     <textLang mainLang="per" otherLangs="ara">Persian and Arabic</textLang>
                     <note>
                        <p>Item n. </p>
                        <p>Untitled note instructing on the recitation of particular prayers ascribed to <persName key="person_f7059" role="ant">Aḥmad Sāvajī</persName>, pupil of <persName key="person_f7263" role="oth">Mawlānā Aḥmad Ardabīlī</persName>. 
                        </p>
                        <p>Not dated at end. 
</p>
                        <p>Fine nastaʿlīq and naskh in the style of Aḥmad Nayrīzī (d. 1722).
</p>
                     </note>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem class="http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2010112936" n="15" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_1180-item15">
                     <locus from="132r" to="137v">ff. 132r-137v</locus>
                     <textLang mainLang="per" otherLangs="ara">Persian and Arabic</textLang>
                     <note>
                        <p>Item o. </p>
                        <p>Untitled Arabic prayer in praise of the <persName key="viaf_97245226" role="subject">Prophet Muḥammad</persName> and all twelve of the <orgName>Is̲nāʾ ʿAsharī Imams</orgName>. 
                        </p>
                        <p>Copied in calligraphic naskh in the style of <persName key="viaf_51041763" role="oth">Aḥmad Nayrīzī</persName> (d. 1722). 
                        </p>
                        <p>Not dated at end.
</p>
                        <p>Annotations in margins. 
</p>
                     </note>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem n="16" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_1180-item16">
                     <locus from="138r" to="140v">ff. 138r-140v</locus>
                     <textLang mainLang="per" otherLangs="ara">Persian and Arabic</textLang>
                     <note>
                        <p>Item p. </p>
                        <p>Untitled commentary on selected verses from the <title>Mas̲navī-yi maʿnavī</title> of <persName key="viaf_98930150" role="ant">Jalāl al-Dīn Rūmī</persName>, with substantial quotations, by an unnamed author. 
                        </p>
                        <p>Not dated at end. 
</p>
                        <p>Fine nastaʿlīq and naskh in the style of <persName key="viaf_51041763" role="oth">Aḥmad Nayrīzī</persName> (d. 1722). Verses arranged into four columns. 
                        </p>
                     </note>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem n="17" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_1180-item17">
                     <locus from="140v" to="142v">ff. 140v-142v</locus>
                     <textLang mainLang="per" otherLangs="ara">Persian and Arabic</textLang>
                     <note>
                        <p>Item q. </p>
                        <p>Guidance for novices of Sufism, with particular reference to the <orgName>Naqshbandī ṭarīqah</orgName>, by the famous saint <persName key="ark:/81055/vdc_100166176979.0x000001 viaf_90042997" role="aut">Nūr al-Dīn ʿAbd al-Raḥmān Jāmī</persName> (d. 898/1492). 
                        </p>
                        <p>Not dated at end. 
</p>
                        <p>Calligraphic nastaʿlīq-i khafī. 
</p>
                     </note>
                     <title xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="work_2858">Bayān-i ṭarīqah-'i khvājagān</title>
                     <title xml:lang="per" key="work_2858">بيان طريقهٴ خواجگان</title>
                     <author>
                        <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" type="supplied" key="ark:/81055/vdc_100166176979.0x000001 viaf_90042997">Jāmī</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="per" type="supplied" key="ark:/81055/vdc_100166176979.0x000001 viaf_90042997">نورالدين عبدالرحمن جامى</persName>
                     </author>
                  </msItem>
               </msContents>
